	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories A Durban pensioner died in a house fire in the Westville area, paramedic services said on Monday. Rescue Care spokesperson Garrith Jamieson said the victim was 70 years old. "He passed away due to severe burns from the fire." It is unclear how the fire started. Jamieson said police and fire services were investigating the incident. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  